<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 6:15PM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Periods Of Light To Moderate Snow This Evening...
Doppler radar indicated bursts of light to moderate snowfall are
ongoing across much of southeast Iowa and west central Illinois.
Snowfall will accumulate a quick one to two inches, mainly on
elevated and grassy areas, through the evening hours.
The main impact will be greatly reduced visibility to less than a
mile in the heavier snowfall.
While roads should remain wet you should use extra caution while
driving due to the low visibility.</description>
